â­ In short:

	You must write a function that:

	âœ” reads a file line by line
	âœ” returns one line per call
	âœ” includes the \n when it exists
	âœ” returns NULL when done
	âœ” works for files and standard input
	âœ” uses a header file and a utils file
	
	
	
	âœ”ï¸ Example in plain English
	
			fd = open("hello.txt", O_RDONLY);


		This does not give you the text.

		It gives you a handle so you can later say:

			read(fd, buffer, BUFFER_SIZE);


		and the OS returns chunks of the file.

	get_next_line() simply wraps this process and returns one line at a time.
